track.name: Reeperbahn
comments: No one else can make "WEARING WOMEN'S UNDERTHINGS" sound this infernal.
Dripping with crackled broken down genius. Like someone has wound up an old demonic gypsy music box in a smokey back room in a carnival of debauched sleaze.
I wish life was a little more like Waits songs... but then I guess I wouldn't need his songs so much... and you can't let that happen, can you? [2]
I cried first time I heard this song. <3

Amazing song, for sure, but I love the way the song starts.  It's like a machine struggling to get its gears moving, then it kicks in full.
I wish life was a little more like Waits songs... but then I guess I wouldn't need his songs so much... and you can't let that happen, can you?
